cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.SE, cs.FL, cs.DS

The paper proposes a new logic for program verification and static analysis, specifically targeting separation logic. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science). The paper also discusses the use of inductive predicates for reasoning about data structures, which suggests a possible connection to cs.PL (Programming Languages). The focus on program verification and static analysis suggests a connection to cs.SE (Software Engineering). The paper also discusses the use of Boolean operators and their limitations, which suggests a possible connection to cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory). Finally, the paper discusses the use of list-segment predicates, which suggests a possible connection to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
